  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Drought affected populations in the Southern districts of Lesotho</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide emergency cash and food assistance to drought-affected people in Qacha&#x2019;s Nek district of Lesotho. WFP will use CERF funds to distribute a combination of cash and commodity vouchers to target households, coupled with social and behavior change communication to enhance their coping capacity. An estimated 13,335 people will benefit from this project, which will be implemented in six months.</narrative>
  </description>
